    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-04-29T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-04-29T06:00:00-05:00" n="442"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d442">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4316: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-04-29T19:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 29, 1922—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 30—12:36 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>182. Diplomatic body met this afternoon and instructed foreign commandants in
                    Tientsin to adhere “as far as lies within the power of the foreign commandants”
                    to the resolutions of the diplomatic body regarding military occupation of the
                    railway from Peking to Shanhaikwan of January 26, 1912; see MacMurray,<note
                        n="32" xml:id="d442fn32">John V. A. MacMurray (ed)., <hi rend="italic"
                            >Treaties and Agreements with and concerning China</hi>, 1894–1919 (New
                        York, Oxford University Press, 1921).</note> volume 1, pages 318 to 319.</p>
                <p>The phrase in quotation marks above was inserted to meet my objection to
                    resolution 4 which provides for resistance by the combined forces of the
                    powers.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
